entry.summary:
There's been a lot of talk about the social network Bluesky lately. If you have an account there and want to show your latest status update on your blog, here's an easy way to do that.
Vincent Will has put together a script named bsky-embed. All you need to do is enter your username and modify the settings to your liking. I've added it to the footer using this setup:
<div class="bluesky">
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bsky-embed/dist/bsky-embed.es.js" async></script>
<bsky-embed
  username="birming.com"
  limit="1"
  load-more="false"
  custom-styles=".border-slate-300 { border: none; }"
>
</bsky-embed>
</div>

The bluesky div class is my own addition, giving the widget a style that matches the Bearming Theme. Here's the CSS styling for that:
/* Bluesky */
.bluesky {
  margin: 30px 0;
  padding: 10px;
  font-family: var(--font-secondary);
  font-size: inherit;
  text-align: left;
  background: var(--accent-color);
  border-radius: 10px;
}

Good luck!

